 for the 'po_filter' url argument"]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin", "bases": ["RosettaBaseMixin"], "methods": [{"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin._request_request", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "default", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin.language_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Determine/return the language id from the url kwargs, after\nvalidating that:\n1. the language is in rosetta_settings.ROSETTA_LANGUAGES, and\n2. the current user is permitted to translate that language\n\n(If either of the above fail, throw a 404.)"]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin.po_file_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Based on the url kwargs, infer and return the path to the .po file to\nbe shown/updated.\n\nThrow a 404 if a file isn't found."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin.po_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the parsed .po file that is currently being translated/viewed.\n\n(Note that this parsing also involves marking up each entry with a hash\nof its contents.)"]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin.po_file_cache_key", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the cache key used to save/access the .po file (when actually\npersisted in cache)."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.RosettaFileLevelMixin.po_file_is_writable", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return True if we're able (in terms of file system permissions) to\nwrite out changes to the .po file we're translating."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Mixin for dealing with views that work specifically with a single\n.po file. In addition to what the super class brings, it adds the following\nproperties:\n* language_id (e.g. 'fr'); derived from url, and validated\n* po_file_path (filesystem path to catalog)\n* po_file (pofile object)\n* po_file_is_writable (bool: do we have filesystem write perms to file)"]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFileListView", "bases": ["RosettaBaseMixin", "TemplateView"], "methods": [{"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFileListView.get_context_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFileListView.http_method_names", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFileListView.template_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Lists the languages, the gettext catalog files that can be translated,\nand their translation progress for a filtered list of apps/projects."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView", "bases": ["RosettaFileLevelMixin", "TemplateView"], "methods": [{"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.fix_nls", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "in_", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "out_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Fixes submitted translations by filtering carriage returns and pairing\nnewlines at the begging and end of the translated string with the original"]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.post", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The only circumstances when we POST is to submit the main form, both\nupdating translations (if any changed) and advancing to the next page of\nmessages.\n\nThere is no notion of validation of this content; as implemented, unknown\nfields are ignored and a generic failure message is shown.\n\nSubmitted changes are saved out to the specified .po file on the\nfilesystem if that file is writable, otherwise the cached version of the\nfile is updated (so it can be downloaded). Then the user is redirected\nto the next page of messages (if there is one; otherwise they're\nredirected back to the current page)."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.get_context_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.ref_lang", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the language id for the \"reference language\" (the language to\nbe translated *from*, if not English).\n\nThrow a 404 if it's not in rosetta_settings.ROSETTA_LANGUAGES."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.ref_lang_po_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a parsed .po file object for the \"reference language\", if one\nexists, otherwise None."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.msg_filter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Validate/return msg_filter from request (e.g. 'fuzzy', 'untranslated'),\nor a default.\n\nIf a query is also specified in the request, then return None."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Strip and return the query (for searching the catalog) from the\nrequest, or None."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.get_entries", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a list of the entries (messages) that would be part of the\ncurrent \"view\"; that is, all of the ones from this .po file matching the\ncurrent query or msg_filter."]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.http_method_names", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFormView.template_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Show a form with a page's worth of messages to be translated; handle its\nsubmission by updating cached pofile and, if possible, writing out changes\nto existing .po file.\n\nQuery strings that affect what's shown:\n* msg_filter: filters which messages are displayed. One of 'all', 'fuzzy',\n  'translated', and 'untranslated'\n* ref_lang: specifies which language should be shown as the source. Only\n  applicable when REF_LANG setting is set to True\n* page: which page (number) should be shown of the paginated results (with\n  msg_filter or query applied)\n* query: a search string, where only matches are shown. Fields that are\n  searched include: source, translated text, \"occurence\" file path, or\n  context hints."]}, {"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFileDownload", "bases": ["RosettaFileLevelMixin", "View"], "methods": [{"name": "rosetta.views.TranslationFileDownload.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, 